52
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:38,080
And one of them is called .mcp.json.

53
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:42,000
And it's a JSON file that describes any MCP servers

54
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,600
that are included inside this plugin.

55
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,199
And so that's where you would put them.

56
00:02:47,199 --> 00:02:51,039
And there's another one called .lsp.json.

57
00:02:51,039 --> 00:02:52,399
And that's something special.

58
00:02:52,399 --> 00:02:56,000
And LSP is something called a Language Server Protocol,

59
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,440
which is something which is able to describe to Cloud Code

60
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,759
the rules of a programming language,

61
00:03:01,759 --> 00:03:05,199
such that it can validate that some code you've written is going to work.

62
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:10,000
And Cloud Code already knows about the common programming languages.

63
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,800
But if you were to work with a new programming language

64
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,880
that Cloud Code isn't already aware of,

65
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:18,320
then you would want to configure that as one of these files.

66
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:21,119
You would put it in a .lsp.json.

67
00:03:21,119 --> 00:03:23,119
And you would put it in that plugin folder

68
00:03:23,119 --> 00:03:27,279
in order for that language to be supported by that plugin.

69
00:03:27,279 --> 00:03:31,199
