00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,679
until we've got sandboxing in place

162
00:06:53,679 --> 00:06:54,959
before you do it perhaps.

163
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,200
And then the third thing is like a mix

164
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,559
of both secure and productive,

165
00:06:59,119 --> 00:07:02,640
which is saying that the approval process

166
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:04,959
that you have in an unsandboxed world

167
00:07:04,959 --> 00:07:07,600
where you say you press the number two to approve something

168
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,920
or the number one if you want to do it step by step,

169
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,040
it's all very well,

170
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:13,839
but there's always a risk of what they call approval fatigue

171
00:07:13,839 --> 00:07:16,239
when you get so used to pressing the number one

172
00:07:16,239 --> 00:07:18,399
that you're just sitting there going one, one, one, one,

173
00:07:18,399 --> 00:07:19,760
and you're not actually reading it.

174
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,160
And so it's basically YOLOing,

175
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:24,559
but you're giving yourself a full sense of security.

176
00:07:24,559 --> 00:07:26,079
And so from that point of view,

177
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:29,920
the unsandboxed approach may not be as safe as you think it is

178
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,519
because your brain gets tuned

179
00:07:31,519 --> 00:07:34,399
to just hitting one or two all the time.

